## 4. Expected Outcomes (Success Metrics)

| Metric | Target Impact |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Cycle Time (Concept to Ready-for-Dev)** | Reduce from **3 weeks** to **3 days** |
| **Rework Rate** | Decrease rework due to "misunderstood requirements" by **50%** |
| **Analyst Satisfaction** | Nurzhan spends **>50%** of time on Analysis (vs. formatting) |
| **Defect Density** | Reduced ambiguous logic bugs in UAT |

---

## 5. Constraints & Notes

*   **Human-in-the-Loop:** The AI is a **copilot**, not an autopilot. Nurzhan must review and approve all generated specifications. The AI does not make business decisions.
*   **Security:** Data must not leave Air Astana’s secure tenancy (Private Cloud deployment required).
*   **Organizational Limits:** The AI can optimize the *handoff*, but it cannot fix broken organizational reporting lines or lack of product strategy (Project vs Product funding model).
